<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06097095 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06097095 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  TORRANCE; MAN; JUVENILE; ARREST; BOMB; ASSAULT; RELIGION; FACILITY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A teen-ager and a 27-year-old transient have been arrested in connection witha string of smoke bomb attacks at Southern California churches and newspaperoffices.;    Police in this Los Angeles suburb arrested Larry Wayne Mitchelland a 17-year-old boy, whose name was withheld, Thursday afternoon at theyouth's home in the city of Bell Gardens, police said. The youth was laterreleased from custody.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  California News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TRANSIENT AND TEEN ARRESTED IN TORRANCE SMOKEBOMBING  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The pair were arrested on suspicion of setting off a foul-smelling bombduring a pastor's sermon at a church here last month, but Torrance police Sgt.Ronald Traber said initial evidence suggests the two could be linked to a rashof smoke bombings, including ones at the Los Angeles Times and the OrangeCounty Register's Santa Ana office.;    Times security officials said theyreceived a call from someone claiming to have left the package, which includeda copy of a Register story about the attack at that newspaper. In the Registerincident, a man claiming to be the Antichrist left the bomb with a letterthreatening several prominent religious leaders.;    Another smoke bombdisrupted a religious service last month at the Crystal Cathedral in GardenGrove, and one blew up at a religious broadcasting studio in Tustin.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Los Angeles Times  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Torrance  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910406  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  207  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday April 6, 199100097095,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, S